---
import AppLayout from "../../../layouts/AppLayout.astro";
---

<AppLayout
  title="Grimora Privacy"
  description="Privacy policy for Grimora, a free native Magic: The Gathering card search and list-building app."
  currentPath="/apps/grimora/privacy"
>
  <article class="contentPage">
    <header class="contentPageHeader">
      <p class="eyebrow">Grimora</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="contentIntro">
        This policy applies to Grimora on iOS, iPadOS, macOS, and visionOS.
      </p>
      <p class="lastUpdated">Last updated: May 20, 2026</p>
    </header>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>Developer Data Collection</h2>
      <p>
        Grimora does not have a Grimora account system, advertising, tracking,
        developer-operated analytics, or sale of personal data. Sam Wagner does
        not operate a Grimora backend that stores your card lists, search
        history, preferences, or card-library data.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>On-Device Storage</h2>
      <p>
        Grimora stores app data on your device so the app can work quickly after
        setup. This can include the local card database, downloaded card images,
        image cache, preferences, search history, and user-created lists.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can remove locally stored Grimora data by deleting the app or by
        using device and system storage controls provided by Apple.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>iCloud And CloudKit</h2>
      <p>
        User-created lists may sync through your Apple ID and iCloud account
        when iCloud is available and enabled for Grimora. Sam Wagner does not
        operate, administer, or access your Apple ID or iCloud account.
      </p>
      <p>
        iCloud availability, sync behavior, and account controls are provided by
        Apple through iOS, iPadOS, macOS, and visionOS.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>External Services</h2>
      <p>
        Grimora downloads card data, card images, pricing data, or related
        Magic: The Gathering metadata from Scryfall and MTGJSON. Those services
        may receive normal network request metadata such as IP address, device
        network details, request time, and requested URLs.
      </p>
      <p>
        Grimora is designed to use local and bulk-style data where possible
        instead of making excessive live API requests.
      </p>
      <div class="linkPanel">
        <p>Relevant third-party documentation:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://scryfall.com/docs/api">Scryfall API docs</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://scryfall.com/docs/api/images">Scryfall card imagery docs</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://scryfall.com/docs/api/rate-limits">Scryfall rate limits</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://scryfall.com/docs/terms">Scryfall terms</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://mtgjson.com/license/">MTGJSON license</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://company.wizards.com/en/legal/fancontentpolicy">Wizards Fan Content Policy</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>Support</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy questions or support requests, use the
        <a href="/apps/grimora/support">Grimora support page</a>.
        Do not include passwords, private Apple ID details, or sensitive personal
        information in support reports.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</AppLayout>
